<HEAD>New-England Per&s;ecutors Laws again&s;t the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ings Subjects.</HEAD>
<P>Have ordered, That every &s;uch Vagabond <HI>Quaker</HI> found within any part of this Juri&s;diction, &s;hall be apprehended by any Per&s;on or Per&s;ons, or by the Con&s;table of the Town, where he or &s;he is found, and by the Con&s;table, or in his ab&s;ence, by any other Per&s;on or Per&s;ons, conveyed b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">fore the next Magi&s;trate of that &s;hire, where they are taken, o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Commi&s;&s;ioner inve&s;ted with Magi&s;tratical Power, and bring by them adjudged to be a wandering <HI>Quaker, viz.</HI> &s;uch that hath no orderly al<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">owance in this Ju|ri<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">diction, and not giving civil Re&s;pect or by any other <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> mani<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e&s;ting him&s;e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> to be a <HI>Quaker,</HI> &s;hall by warrant under the hand of the &s;aid Magi&s;trate or Commi&s;&s;ioner&punc; directed to the Con&s;table of the Town, or to any other meet Per&s;on&punc; be &s;tripped from the middle, upward, and tyed to a Carts Fa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">l, and whipped through the Town, and from thence Immediately conveyed to the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">on&s;table of the next Town towards the b<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rder, of our J<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">i&s;diction, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> their Warrant &s;hall direct&punc; til the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> conveyed through the outward mo&s;t Towns of our juri&s;diction</P>
<P><HI>Ob<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">erve</HI> That <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> the follow<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ng <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> of their many W<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">rants of the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Blood<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> Whipping of the Innocent <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> who by the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> allow|ance to trade, buy or &s;e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">l with<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> for which cau&s;e of being &s;o prohibit<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d, and found with <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> of Juri&s;diction, are by them called <HI>Vagabonds,</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> being found, as <HI>Cain</HI> was, to have no dwelling in i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> are the right time <HI>Vagabonds,</HI> endeavouring (as much as <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span">) to whip others from their certain dwellings <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> to become <HI>Vagabonds</HI> like them&s;elves.</P>
